      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The applicant must be a permanent resident of Haryana and possess a valid Parivar Pehchan Patra (PPP).\n1. The applicant must own land or have a registered lease of at least 10 years, free from legal encumbrances.\n1. The applicant must have access to a water source such as a canal, well, tube well, or similar.\n1. The applicant must be trained in aquaculture or fisheries and hold a valid certification.\n1. The applicant must be willing to maintain and operate the system at their own cost post-installation.\n1. The applicant must submit a Detailed Project Report (DPR) or a Self-Contained Proposal (SCP).\n1. The applicant must sign an agreement with the Fisheries Department to be eligible under the scheme.\n\n",
